title: Energy and Angular Distributions of Photoneutrons Produced By 70-Mev X-Rays.

x4freetext: ENERGY AND ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS OF PHOTONEUTRONS
PRODUCED BY 70-MEV X-RAYS.

x4codes.hlp: National Research Council, Ottawa, Ontario, Canada

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Canadian Journal of Physics, Vol.33, p.785 (1955)

x4codes.hlp: National Research Council, Ottawa, Ontario, Canada

x4freetext: THE LENGTH OF THE X-RAY PULSE IS ABOUT 200 MICROSEC.
ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS WERE APPROXIMATED WITH A FORM
A + B*SIN**2 .
STATISTICAL ERRORS ARE PRESENTED.
FOR THE HEAVY ELEMENTS THE ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS ARE
ESSENTIALLY ISOTROPIC, INDICATING THE PREDOMINANCE OF
THE EVAPORATION PROCESS, WHILE FOR THE LIGHT ELEMENTS
THERE IS ALSO AN ANISOTROPIC COMPONENT PEAKED AT 90
DEGREES. THE ENERGY DISTRIBUTIONS SHOW THAT MOST OF
NEUTRONS CAN BE ATTRIBUTED TO AN EVAPORATION PROCESS
WHICH IS GOVERNED BY A CONSTANT NUCLEAR TEMPERATURE.
A HIGH-ENERGY TAIL IS ATTRIBUTED TO DIRECT INTERACTION.
.DATA WERE COMPILED IN SCJAD OF SARATOV STATE
UNIVERSITY.
CORRECTED BY V.VARLAMOV, V.MCLANE
